The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, April 09, 2004  Calcutta Column

	The area near Curzon Park and Shahid Minar turns into a criminals den after dark. Ruffians harass and rob people waiting for buses. Authorities are requested to depute plainclothed policemen in the area to ensure security.
	 B.N.Bose, Dum Dum 
	A prominent English medium school in central Calcutta has instructed its students to buy books from a particular book store in the vicinity. While shops in College Street allow discounts up to 25 per cent, this shop does not give any. It is quite apparent that the school authorities are augmenting their revenue through an arrangement with the shop. 
	Rabindranath Kar, Sankar Ghosh Lane 
	Eastern Railways should introduce at least two trains between Naihati and Diamond Harbour, like a Canning-Bongaon local. 
	Biman Saha, Lake Town 

